---
import DefaultLayout from '../../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import FullWidth from '../../components/FullWidth.astro'
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/QueryIsolationComparisonTable.astro'
import FeaturePillar from '../../components/FeaturePillar.astro'
import { Link } from 'accessible-astro-components'

const technicalPillars = [
  {
    index: "01",
    title: "Ephemeral Pod Sandboxing",
    description: "Icebreaker moves the isolation boundary from the 'Warehouse' to the individual query.",
    items: [
      "<strong>Zero Persistence:</strong> Every query runs in a dedicated K8S pod that is created on-demand and destroyed immediately upon completion.",
      "<strong>Physical Separation:</strong> Unlike logical resource groups, pods provide a hard kernel-level boundary for CPU and memory."
    ]
  },
  {
    index: "02",
    title: "DataFusion Engine",
    description: "The 'Secret Sauce' that makes atomic isolation fast enough for production use.",
    items: [
      "<strong>Sub-Second Startup:</strong> By utilizing a lightweight, Rust-based engine, Icebreaker avoids the 'Cold Start' penalty of heavy JVM warehouses.",
      "<strong>In-Memory Safety:</strong> Data is processed entirely within the volatile memory of the pod and never touches persistent shared storage."
    ]
  },
  {
    index: "03",
    title: "VPC-Native Execution",
    description: "Your data never leaves your perimeter, and your queries never share a process.",
    items: [
      "<strong>Network Isolation:</strong> Each execution pod is governed by your VPC’s security groups and IAM roles at the task level.",
      "<strong>Multi-Tenant Integrity:</strong> Physically isolate sensitive HR or financial data queries from general-purpose AI agent traffic."
    ]
  }
];
---

<DefaultLayout title="Query Isolation | Icebreaker Data">
    <section>
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="text-center text-6xl md:text-left">
                Query Isolation
            </h1>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8">
        <div class="container">
            <p class="text-2xl">
                Guarantee the secure and successful execution of every query. 
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <FullWidth>
        <div class="container grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center py-12">
            <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border-t-4 border-(--primary-400) bg-(--neutral-900)/10">
                <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">The Noisy Neighbor Problem</h4>
                <ul class="list-warning text-lg space-y-4">
                    <li><strong>Cluster Contention:</strong> Background pipelines starve mission-critical dashboards of CPU cycles.</li>
                    <li><strong>Agentic Bloat:</strong> AI agents submit thousands of small requests on oversized compute.</li>
                    <li><strong>Security Fragility:</strong> Logical RBAC is hard to manage; a physical security boundary works.</li>
                    <li><strong>Shared JVM Risk:</strong> A single query can crash an entire warehouse or cluster.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p class="text-xl opacity-80">
                    Traditional warehouses rely on <strong>Logical Isolation</strong>. You segment by department or warehouse size, but under the hood, queries are still fighting for the same memory heap and thread pools. 
                </p>
                <br/>
                <p class="text-xl opacity-80">
                    Icebreaker uses hyperscaler-grade, atomic <strong>Query Isolation</strong>. We decouple the execution from the cluster, ensuring every query—no matter how 'greedy'—has its own private lane.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </FullWidth>

<section class="bg-(--secondary-400) py-24">
    <div class="container">
        <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl rounded-3xl bg-white p-10 md:p-16 shadow-2xl text-(--neutral-800) relative overflow-hidden">
            
            <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-(--primary-500) clip-path-poly opacity-10"></div>

            <header class="mb-10">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-(--primary-500) mb-4">
                    <span class="border-2 border-(--primary-500) px-2 py-1 rounded">Key Concept</span>
                    <span>•</span>
                    <span>3 Min Read</span>
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-(--primary-500) leading-tight">
                    What is Query Isolation?
                </h2>
            </header>

                <div>
                    <p>
                        x
                    </p><br/>
                    

                    <p>
                        By running a lightweight <strong>DataFusion</strong> engine inside a standalone K8S pod, we achieve physical resource enclosure. If an AI agent goes rogue and attempts to consume excessive memory, it hits a hard limit at the pod level. It cannot "leak" into the memory space of your executive dashboard query running on the same underlying node. 
                    </p><br/>

                    <p>
                        This isn't just about performance—it's about <strong>Security.</strong> True multi-tenancy requires that sensitive data queries are physically segmented at the execution layer. In Icebreaker, once a query is finished, its pod is destroyed. There is zero persistence, zero residue, and zero shared state.
                    </p><br/>

                    <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-(--primary-500) bg-(--neutral-100) p-6 my-8 rounded-r-xl">
                        <p class="text-xl italic font-semibold text-(--primary-500) mb-0">
                            x
                        </p><br/>
                    </blockquote>

                    <p>
                        Managing thousands of concurrent, isolated pods requires a level of orchestration that traditional warehouses were not built for. 
                        That's where the Icebreaker <Link href="/product/demand-shaping">Demand Shaping</Link> comes in, ensuring that while every query 
                        is isolated, the underlying infrastructure remains perfectly optimized for each and every job.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="mb-16 text-center">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">The "How": Technical Pillars</h2>
                <p class="text-xl mx-auto opacity-80">
                    The architecture that makes atomic query isolation possible.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-12">
                {technicalPillars.map((pillar) => (
                    <FeaturePillar 
                        index={pillar.index}
                        title={pillar.title}
                        description={pillar.description}
                        listItems={pillar.items}
                    />
                ))}
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <FullWidth>
        <div class="container py-12">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Comparing Isolation Models</h2>
            <ComparisonTable title="Comparison between Traditional Warehouses and Icebreaker Data" />
        </div>
    </FullWidth>
</DefaultLayout>